main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright, luminous object in the sky for 16 minutes on September 23, 1965.
interesting points: The object remained in one place, The witness observed it through a telescope at a 600-degree azimuth, The object had no visible trail or unusual features, The sighting was confirmed by a civilian source considered reliable, The report indicates no physical evidence was found.
witness description: civilian who used a telescope for observation
